useradd 
-D --> to view or change the default values used by useradd command
	-g --> manual default GID 
	-b --> manual default home directory base 
	-f --> manual default inactive grace period 
	-e --> manual default expire value 
	-s --> manual default shell 
	-k --> manual default skeleton (SKEL) directory 
-u --> manual UID
-g --> manual GID or group name for primary group configuration 
-G --> to specify a comma-separated list of supplementary group names or numbers
-M --> do not create user home directory
-m --> create the user home directory
-b --> manual user home directory base
-d --> to specify a home directory (or a new home directory) for the user
-k --> to specify the skeleton (SKEL) directory for the user (-m required)
-s --> to specify a shell
-c --> GECOS (General Electric Comprehensive Operating System) field; typically used to provide the user's full name.
